      "message": "I think we\u0027ll want to record metrics for failure here too.\n\nWhat kind of work does crash_reporter do?\nNormally, we\u0027d record something like Metrics::CrashSkippedReason::kUploadFailed if Crashpad failed the upload. Maybe that\u0027d be appropriate.\n\nAlso, DoubleForkAndExec() is intended for situations where we explicitly *don\u0027t* want to be responsible for waiting for the child, but that also means we can\u0027t determine whether it ultimately succeeded or not. I think there\u0027s no reason Crashpad can\u0027t waitpid() for crash_reporter to finish and doing so would allow us to definitively record metrics about its success.",
